# UI Design System — Warm & Simple

## Design Philosophy

Build interfaces that feel like a personal journal: warm, uncluttered, and trustworthy.
Every pixel should serve clarity, not decoration.

---

## Color Tokens (CSS Custom Properties)

Always reference colors via CSS variables. Never hardcode hex values in component styles.

```scss
// Primary action (warm indigo)
--color-primary: #5c67f2
--color-primary-hover: #4a55e8
--color-primary-light: #eef0ff

// Background layers (warm off-white progression)
--color-bg: #faf9f6         // Page background
--color-surface: #ffffff    // Cards, inputs, panels
--color-sidebar: #f2f0eb    // Left sidebar

// Text hierarchy
--color-text: #2c2820           // Primary — warm dark
--color-text-secondary: #6b7280 // Secondary
--color-text-muted: #9ca3af     // Metadata, placeholders

// Borders (subtle, warm-tinted)
--color-border: #e5e3de
--color-border-light: #eeece8

// Semantic
--color-success: #2d7a4f        // Text
--color-success-bg: #f0fdf4
--color-success-border: #bbf7d0
--color-error: #c0392b
--color-error-bg: #fef2f2
--color-error-border: #fecaca

// Accent — Memory (amber warmth)
--color-memory-bg: #fffbeb
--color-memory-border: #fde68a
--color-memory-tag-bg: #fef3c7
--color-memory-tag-border: #fcd34d

// Accent — Persona Evolution
--color-evolve-green-bg: #f0fdf4
--color-evolve-green-border: #bbf7d0
--color-evolve-blue-bg: #eff6ff
--color-evolve-blue-border: #bfdbfe

// Chat bubbles
--color-user-bubble: #eef0ff        // Light indigo for user
--color-user-label: #5c67f2
--color-assistant-bubble: #f5f4f0   // Warm gray for AI
--color-assistant-label: #6b7280
```

