## Responsive Design

Breakpoints (mobile-first):

```scss
$bp-sm: 640px;    // Small phones
$bp-md: 768px;    // Tablets
$bp-lg: 1024px;   // Small laptops
$bp-xl: 1280px;   // Standard desktops
```

Layout adaptation:
- `< 768px`: Sidebar collapses to drawer (hidden by default, toggle button)
- `768px - 1024px`: Sidebar at 280px, chat bubbles max-width 88%
- `> 1024px`: Full layout, sidebar 320px, bubbles max-width 78%

```scss
// Pattern
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .drawer { position: fixed; z-index: 100; transform: translateX(-100%); }
  .drawer.open { transform: translateX(0); }
}
```

---

## Anti-Patterns (Never Do)

- ❌ Hardcode colors: `color: #06c` → use `var(--color-primary)`
- ❌ Use `!important` — fix specificity instead
- ❌ `margin: auto` on flex children without `min-width: 0`
- ❌ `display: block` inside flex containers where flex is sufficient
- ❌ Pure black shadows: `rgba(0,0,0,0.1)` → use warm dark `rgba(44,40,32,...)`
- ❌ Font sizes below `0.7rem` for readable content
- ❌ Border radius inconsistency — always use tokens
- ❌ Inline styles in Angular TypeScript — extract to `styles: []` array or SCSS file
- ❌ CSS `em` units for spacing — use `rem` for predictable scaling
- ❌ Overusing borders AND shadows together — choose one for depth

